title: Marysville man shoots adult son
text:
A 30-year-old man was shot by his 64-year-old father Friday night on 72nd St NE in Marysville.
Snohomish County Sheriff says the suspect was arrested on a charge of first-degree domestic violence assault with a weapon.
The wife of the suspect called police saying that her husband was trying to shoot her as she fled the location.
Deputies responding to the scene found the victim with a gunshot wound to the abdomen.
He was transported to Providence Regional Medical Center in unknown condition.
